INSERT INTO `redc_faq` (`faqid`, `fcatid`, `question`, `answer`, `isactive`) VALUES
(24, 8, 'How long it will take to process my application?', 'For most of our programmes, the admissions committee begins reviewing applications three to four weeks prior to the programme start date. Once the review process begins, applicants are notified via email regarding the status of their application.\r\n\r\nTo check the status of a current application, please contact us by phone: +92-42-5722142, fax: +92-42-5722691, or email: rec@lums.edu.pkThis e-mail address is being protected from spam bots, you need JavaScript enabled to view it', 'Y'),
(23, 8, 'What are the admissions requirements?', 'Each programme description defines in detail who the programme is targeted at and what a typical participant profile will be.  These guidelines can be used while nominating participants.  Nominating authorities are encouraged to nominate individuals with a record of accomplishment, demonstrated ability and promise.   Programmes are conducted in English and it is essential for participants to be proficient in English to participant.', 'Y'),
(25, 8, 'When will I receive the confirmation letter?', 'Approximately one week prior to the start of the programme, you will receive a confirmation packet, including confirmation letter, invoice, FAQs & Road map to LUMS.', 'Y'),
(21, 7, 'Where is REDC located?', 'REDC is located on the campus of Lahore University of Management Sciences, Lahore, Pakistan. The address is as follows: \r\n\r\nRausing Executive Development Centre\r\nLahore University of Management Sciences\r\nOpposite Sector "U", Defence Housing Authority\r\nLahore - 54792, Pakistan.\r\n\r\nOnce you reach the campus, the guards at the gate will be able to guide you to REDC.', 'N'),
(22, 8, 'How can I register for a programme?', 'Each REDC programme has its own set of admissions criteria. There are two simple ways to apply:\r\n\r\n    * Apply online at http://redc.lums.edu.pk by selecting a particular programme\r\n    * Request an application by surface mail or by email at rec@lums.edu.pkThis e-mail address is being protected from spam bots, you need JavaScript enabled to view it\r\n\r\nFor additional questions, please feel free to contact our Assistant Manager Marketing at:\r\n\r\n+92-42-5722142, 5722670-9 Ext 3220, 2335', 'Y'),
(20, 7, 'What is Rausing Executive Development Centre (REDC)?', 'The Rausing Executive Development Centre, a purpose-built facility for training and accommodation, was made possible by a generous contribution from the Rausing family of Sweden. It is used for both Open-Enrolment and Client-Specific programmes of REDC as well as for an in-house training facility for multinationals and local corporations.', 'Y'),
(62, 7, 'How to book a room in REDC?', 'Please contact Mr. Naveed at5 ext 2222', 'Y'),
(27, 9, 'Where do LUMS conduct its executive programmes?', 'Programmes are conducted at the Rausing Executive Centre on the campus of Lahore University of Management Sciences unless otherwise stated.', 'Y'),
(28, 9, 'How long are your programmes?', 'On an average, our programmes start at 8:30 in the morning and end at 7:00 in the evening. There are two breaks for morning and evening tea and one for lunch at around noon.  In some of our programmes there are also evening activities scheduled that may run later than 7:00 pm.', 'Y'),
(29, 9, 'How much time can I expect to spend on course work each day?', 'On average, you will spend four hours each day in the classroom—attending three different classes—although schedules may vary. The rule of thumb is that each class or case study requires two hours advance preparation time that include individual preparation and group discussion.', 'Y'),
(30, 9, 'Do I get any reading material before the start of the programme?', 'We do not send any reading material (unless it is a programme requirement) before the programme. Participants will get the folder with schedule, cases and readings at the time of check-in or registration.', 'Y'),
(31, 9, 'How can I receive more information on LUMS programmes?', 'To know more about LUMS programmes click here .\r\n \r\nFor additional questions, please feel free to contact our Assistant Manager Marketing at:\r\n\r\n+92-42-5722142, 5722670-9  Ext 3220, 2335', 'Y'),
(32, 9, 'Do I get a certificate at the end?', 'Yes, you will get a certificate of attendance at the end.', 'Y'),
(33, 9, 'Does REDC offer client specific programme?', 'We do offer tailor made programmes specific to your organisation’s needs.  We have designed custom programmes for a wide variety of organisations.  We work with you to deliver a learning opportunity that truly fits your organisation and is relevant to your business strategies, challenges and opportunities.  For more information click .', 'Y'),
(34, 10, 'What is the usual class size?', 'Most classes have between 30 and 40 executives.', 'Y'),
(35, 10, 'What teaching methods are used?', 'The senior faculty of LUMS incorporates the latest research and business concepts into the classroom teaching through case studies, lectures, video/computer simulations, business games and small group activities. We offer an interactive learning experience for you to develop personal and professional strengths and lead your organization into an increasingly competitive environment.', 'Y'),
(36, 10, 'How much time can I expect to spend on coursework each day?', 'Usually you spent eight hours each day on course. Typical day of the course is:\r\n09:00 – 10:10 am               Class Session\r\n10:10 – 10:30 am               Tea Break\r\nHowever, there may be variations to suit the required needs of each day according to the programme.', 'Y'),
(37, 10, 'How much time can I expect to spend on coursework each day?', 'Usually you spent eight hours each day on course. Typical day of the course is:\r\n09:00 – 10:10 am               Class Session\r\n10:10 – 10:30 am               Tea Break\r\nHowever, there may be variations to suit the required needs of each day according to the programme.', 'Y'),
(38, 11, 'When the payment is due?', 'Payment is due upon receipt of the invoice. Please note that after the receipt of the invoice, all policies related to cancellation, substitute and transfer apply. Also, ensure that the payment is made before the start of the programme.', 'Y'),
(39, 11, 'How do I pay?', 'Payment can be paid by check or banker’s draft payable to Lahore University of\r\nManagement Sciences. We also accept cash payment.', 'Y'),
(40, 11, 'Can I pay by Credit Card?', 'We do accept payments through Credit Cards (VISA & MASTERCARD only). Our staff would be more than happy to guide you.', 'Y'),
(41, 11, 'What is included in the programme fee?', 'The programme fee includes tuition costs, reading material, snacks and meals served during the programme.', 'Y'),
(42, 12, 'How far is LUMS from the Lahore airport?', 'Depending on traffic, it can take between 20 and 40 minutes to get to LUMS.', 'Y'),
(43, 12, 'Is there any pick and drop service available?', 'We do not provide any pick and drop service to the participants. Participants are expected to make their own arrangements. For your convenience, LUMS road map is provided on the website.', 'Y'),
(45, 13, 'Where will I stay and how much will it cost?', 'You will stay at Rausing Executive Centre at LUMS. For each programme, the participants have been given special discounted residential package, which varies from programme to programme.', 'Y'),
(46, 13, 'What does the residence package include?', 'The residence package given separately for each programme includes full-board accommodation, breakfast, and dinner for the duration of the programme. However, any extra charges such as telephones, extra meals, laundry, etc. will be paid on departure.', 'Y'),
(47, 13, 'If required, can I stay an additional night besides those included in the residence package?', 'Early check-ins and late checkouts are permitted for an additional fee. Please contact the programme manager for availability and charges if you plan on increasing the duration of your stay.', 'Y'),
(48, 13, 'What are the bedrooms like?', 'The bedrooms are designed for single accommodation. Each bedroom has attached bathroom, and it is equipped with mini-bar, writing desk, direct dial NWD/ISD telephone and TV with cable facility. Hairdryer and iron are available on request. Visit  our virtual tour to see the bedroom.', 'Y'),
(49, 13, 'Do the bedrooms have computers?', 'Bedrooms do not have computers but they are Internet ready. You can hook-up your laptop in the rooms.', 'Y'),
(50, 13, 'Are laundry services available?', 'Both laundry and dry cleaning services are available. However, participants may iron their clothes themselves. Irons are available on request.', 'Y'),
(51, 13, 'What other facilities would be available during the programme?', 'The other facilities include:\r\n\r\nFax, Photocopy and Internet /Email. The charges for fax and photocopy are not included in the programme fee and are expected to be cleared at reception on checkout time. Tere are no charges for accessing the Internet.', 'Y'),
(52, 13, 'How can I get daily provisions while staying at REC?', 'A super store, providing items of general provision, is located inside LUMS, which remains open from 10:30am until midnight. In addition, a post office and bank are located near the campus.', 'Y'),
(53, 13, 'Am I allowed to bring my spouse along to stay at REC?', 'You may bring your spouse with you at additional charges. We have a limited number of suites; therefore, please contact the marketing officer for its availability and charges.', 'Y'),
(54, 13, 'Where will I have my meals?', 'Meals are served in self-service Executive Dining Centre near REC. Please let us know in advance if you have any special dietary requirements.', 'Y'),
(55, 13, 'Can I get dinner if I arrive late, the night before the programme begins?', 'Packed meal can be arranged for you, if we are notified about your late arrival in advance.', 'Y'),
(56, 14, 'What is the attire of for an executive during a programme?', 'There is no special dress code for the programmes. Participants are expected to dress casual or business casual.', 'Y'),
(57, 15, 'Cancellation/Substitutes/Transfers and Refunds', 'If an executive is unable to attend a registered course, we will accept a substitute by/till 2 working days before the start of the programme. Substitute candidates will be subject to the same selection process as the original candidate.\r\nIf you wish to cancel your name from a programme, please inform us one week before the start of the programme. Course fee will be refunded after deducting an amount of Rs 3,000/-', 'Y'),
(58, 16, 'Information about Lahore', 'Lahore is the capital city of the province of the Punjab, and the second most populated city in Pakistan. Lahore is also known as the Gardens of the Mughals or City of Gardens, after the significant rich heritage of the Mughal Empire. It is located near the river Ravi and the Indian border, Wagah.\r\nDue to Lahore’s rich history, the Mughal and colonial architecture has still been preserved in all its splendour.', 'Y'),
(59, 16, 'Weather', 'The climate of Lahore is very healthy and salubrious. Except for some days in summer Lahore is a pleasant place to live. There are two main seasons, namely the winter and the summer.\r\nGenerally, the summer begins in April and tapers off in September.  In the peak of summer in June and July the temperature ranges from 38&#8304;C to 44&#8304;C.  October-March are considered winter months although December and January are the coldest months where the temperature ranges from 05&#8304;C to 20&#8304;C', 'Y'),
(60, 17, 'NORMS @ LUMS', 'Following are some of the norms of the university:\r\n\r\n*Please adhere to local/social norms related to dress, drugs, alcohol and personal behavior\r\n*All buildings on campus are non-smoking. You are requested to respect the non smoking laws of the University.\r\n*Littering on campus is highly unacceptable.', 'Y'),
(61, 17, 'Security', 'ndividual are urged to take all possible steps to safeguard themselves and their property. Please remember to take proper precautions to protect your valuables. Never leave cash lying around in your bedroom, and remember to close all doors securely as you enter and leave buildings. Do not leave valuables in classroom or syndicate rooms in between classes or overnight. REDC/LUMS is not responsible for any loss of personal property.', 'Y');

