(4, 13, 'Financial Derivatives: Managing Risk in Troubled Times', '2010-02-16', '2010-02-19', '2010-01-26', 'LUMS, Lahore', '<p>The recent global financial meltdown highlights an important aspect which is that the markets need thorough understanding when dealing with Financial Derivatives. Any confusion related to the use of the various tools and techniques of Financial Derivatives can lead to a disaster with enormous negative repercussions on the world markets. Since every organization is now part of the global marketplace and therefore gets impacted by any turmoil in the financial market which directly affects the bottom line of the organization.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBeing part of the bigger market, the need for the organizations to manage their risks will always be there and hence every organization requires risk mitigation strategies and tools. Choosing the right tools and when to use them are the key success factors to guard against risk. There exist many types of financial derivatives and every derivative has its own suitability and applicability to hedge against risk. Realizing this critical need, REDC has designed a programme keeping in view the needs of financial and non-financial executives to develop a better grasp of the derivatives. The programme gives the required confidence to the participants to successfully use the most suitable derivatives to add enormous value to a firm and to an individual portfolio and reduce any impact emanating from the world markets. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhile the theory as well as the practice of employing these derivatives might at first glance appear advanced and difficult, however, the intent of this programme is to explore the derivatives at a fundamental level and hence make it quite accessible to the participants. <br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '<p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop better understanding at a fundamental level about the derivatives and their use as a risk mitigation tool<br />\r\n2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand the role and use of derivatives as a hedging mechanism and an investment tool<br />\r\n3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand the suitability of derivatives to your company&rsquo;s business model and hedging requirements<br />\r\n4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand availability and suitability of various types of derivatives and their use to alter the distribution of returns on portfolios<br />\r\n5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use of the derivatives in Pakistan and their application in the context of local financial market <br />\r\n6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Explore some of the well-known derivative pricing models to better understand the dynamics of pricing<br />\r\n7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Study key techniques in the Financial Engineering<br />\r\n8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Appreciate the critical role of derivatives in the global financial market and manage risk<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Introduction to Derivatives, Forwards and Futures<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Interest Rate Futures and Swaps<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Forwards, Futures and Swaps in Pakistan<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Introduction to Options and Binomial Option Pricing Model<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Derivative function in Excel and Monte-Carlo Valuation<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Credit Risk and Credit Derivatives and Value-At-Risk (VAR)<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Interest Rate Derivatives<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Financial Engineering and Applications: Employee Stock Options and Real Options<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Recent derivatives mishaps and lessons for the future<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Senior management of financial and nonfinancial institutions, risk managers, fund managers, analysts, corporate treasurers, and regulatory officials can benefit from this programme, either as a refresher course or as a first introduction to the exciting world of financial derivatives. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn addition, executives in every functional area of responsibility, in all industries, whose decisions have significant financial impact, will benefit from this programme as well. Members of corporate boards also seeking a better financial foundation in this area will find this programme valuable. A familiarity with basic financial concepts such as discounting is necessary. However, this programme assumes minimal to no prior knowledge of financial derivatives.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '<p>The senior faculty of LUMS incorporates the latest research and business concepts into the classroom teaching through <strong>case studies, lectures, video/computer simulations, and small group activities</strong>. We offer an interactive, actioanable learning experience for you to develop personal and professional strengths and lead your organisation into an increasingly competitive environment.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>The case method of teaching is a special strength of LUMS.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe university is at the forefront in developing and using cases in its various programmes. Cases describe actual business situations and bring into the classroom, problems and opportunities faced by practicing managers. The participants analyse problems, evaluate alternatives and recommend appropriate solutions which help enhance decision-making abilities, and problem-solving skills.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo enrich the learning process REDC faculty shares its experience and knowledge culled from the latest academic literature and research, as well as insights gained from working with companies as researchers, consultants, and board members. The extensive experience of the faculty in planning and conducting executive programmes ensures an interactive and stimulating classroom experience for you.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Peer group learning is an integral part of the learning process.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe dynamic exchange of knowledge and experience among successful individuals from different organisations and functions enhances learning. Valuable ideas and insights are shared with fellow participants and faculty in and out of the classroom. Group study provides a forum where you benefit from the diversity of views, perspectives and abilities of other team members. Our programme also provides excellent <strong>networking opportunities.</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 46, '<p>Associate Professor, Finance &amp; Associate Dean, Academic Programmes<br />\r\nPhD, University of Manchester<br />\r\nMA, Acadia University<br />\r\nGraduate School of Business<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nWhile at Manchester, Dr Ali worked as a teaching assistant and a researcher for the International Banking Centre. Case studies developed by him have been used at LUMS, Judge Institute of Management, University of Cambridge, and the Manchester Business School. He has published in the Journal of Economics and Business (1993), Financial Director (1993), and Research Newsletter (1995). He also presented a paper at the EDAMBA Conference at Luven, Belgium, 1994. As part of the LUMS-Essex research collaboration, Dr Ali has worked on financial sector and new financial instrument development in Pakistan. He is also the co-editor of Corporate Finance in Pakistan: Case Studies from an Emerging Market, published by OUP. His research interests are in corporate finance, privatization policy, and regulation of utilities.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Research Interests</strong><br />\r\nCorporate Finance; Privatisation Policy; Regulation of Utilities; <br />\r\nFinancial Institutions &amp; Markets and Social Enterprise</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style="font-size: larger;"><strong>Co-Programme Director</strong></span><br />\r\nAli Khalil Malik<br />\r\nPhD, University of Manchester</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Research Interests</strong><br />\r\nFinancial Economics; Financial Econometrics; Financial Mathematics; <br />\r\nEmpirical and Mathematical Modelling of Equities and Derivative Securities<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '', '<p><strong>Programme Fee: Rs 54,000</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The fee includes tuition cost, reading material, tea and lunch served during the programme. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you wish to avail accommodation at LUMS, there will be additional fee of Rs 30,000. It includes accommodation, breakfasts and dinners for the duration of the programme. However, any extra charges such as telephones, extra meals etc should be paid on departure. You may check-in on the evening preceding the start date of the programme and check out the morning after the programme ends. You are, however, requested to inform us of the time of your arrival and departure.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe offer single bed accommodation at the Rausing Executive Centre. Each bedroom with attached bathroom is equipped with mini-fridge, writing desk and direct dial STD/ISD telephone and cable TV. All bedrooms at REC are internet-ready. <em>Please note we do not provide accommodation for drivers accompanying participants.</em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Special Discount Offer</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nBy registering for both the derivative programs together you will benefit from the specially discounted fee of Rs 85,000 (20% discount over aggregate fee of Rs 98,000). <br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<meta content="text/html; charset=utf-8" http-equiv="Content-Type">\r\n<meta content="Word.Document" name="ProgId">\r\n<meta content="Microsoft Word 12" name="Generator">\r\n<meta content="Microsoft Word 12" name="Originator">\r\n<link href="file:///C:\\DOCUME~1\\user\\LOCALS~1\\Temp\\msohtmlclip1\\01\\clip_filelist.xml" rel="File-List" />\r\n<link href="file:///C:\\DOCUME~1\\user\\LOCALS~1\\Temp\\msohtmlclip1\\01\\clip_themedata.thmx" rel="themeData" />\r\n<link href="file:///C:\\DOCUME~1\\user\\LOCALS~1\\Temp\\msohtmlclip1\\01\\clip_colorschememapping.xml" rel="colorSchemeMapping" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<w:Late