(11, 5, 'Management Development Programme', '2009-10-19', '2009-10-30', '2009-10-02', 'LUMS, Lahore', '<p>Managing across functions is a balancing act. Made more challenging in today&rsquo;s new economy, by complex market dynamics and fast-paced competition. Businesses which accomplish a strategic direction, in sync with their inherent functional strengths, respond to the market turbulence better and quicker.&nbsp; Businesses which can strategically evolve to match the market dynamics and economic swings are a step ahead of the competition. To drive performance in this fast paced yet uncertain environment, general managers in the organizations need to operate with an innovative mindset in order to orchestrate the performance of all the functions in harmony.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Management Development Programme (MDP) is a flagship executive education programme developed for functional managers, business unit heads and other professionals who are planning successful career transitions from functional levels to general management levels. The programme allows the participants to expand their knowledge base across all functional areas and develop a holistic management perspective. By integrating key functional disciplines, the participants develop the capability to envision, influence, control or implement the strategic direction of the firm.&nbsp; Residing together at LUMS, the participants immerse themselves in a two week-long learning experience that has been engineered to be rigorous, real in context and transformational.</p>', '<p>Top general management positions usually hold the pulse of an organization and often find themselves in a position where they have to make complex management decisions and lead performance across key functions. The Management Development Programme at LUMS enables the participants to integrate key functional areas in an organization and drive a result-focused business strategy. The objective of MDP is to create successful general managers who can compete and succeed by leveraging their own and their organizations&rsquo; inherent strengths in an integrated manner.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Management Development Programme will help participants;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Acquire conceptual skills to understand business functions and their inter relationships.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop the ability to rethink business functions and lead change at different levels of an organization.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand how industry structures work and evaluate how to create value and profit for their operating unit in a competitive environment.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop key value drivers for their business performance to achieve long-term growth and sustenance.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Learn international best practices as to how organizations respond to recession and cyclicality.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand and harness your leadership capability to lead the organization effectively&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Gain from networking opportunities with like-minded people from diverse backgrounds and industry experiences.</p>', '<p>MDP curriculum has been designed to impart&nbsp; learning which re-enforces functional knowledge and bridges the core management areas of marketing, finance, operations, technology, leadership and team management, with a view to create functional synergies. The curriculum has been mapped into two week-long modules.&nbsp; <br />\r\n<br />\r\nModule 1 has been designed to cover the broad functional areas in order to enhance the general management skills and expose participants to other areas of management in which they may have limited knowledge and/or activities. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nModule 2 focuses on the abilities of the participants to view the organization from a strategic perspective and in the process sharpen their leadership, interpersonal and negotiation skills. This would increase their impact as leaders and change agents.&nbsp; In addition to these key curriculum areas, we would also be focusing on enhancing the abilities of the participants to manage in turbulent times keeping in view the current state of the global economy. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nBased on the core pedagogy of case-based teaching, the programme&rsquo;s curriculum encompasses the latest development in management theory and practice. This includes a repository of local, regional and international case studies that deepens the perspectives from various geographical dimensions. Computer simulations, interactive lectures, exercises and role plays augment case studies to ensure that the learning is delivered and received in a practical context. Below are broad topics indicative of the content that will be covered in Management Development Programme:<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">\r\n<meta name="ProgId" content="Word.Document">\r\n<meta name="Generator" content="Microsoft Word 12">\r\n<meta name="Originator" content="Microsoft Word 12">\r\n<link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:\\DOCUME~1\\user\\LOCALS~1\\Temp\\msohtmlclip1\\01\\clip_filelist.xml" />\r\n<link rel="themeData" href="file:///C:\\DOCUME~1\\user\\LOCALS~1\\Temp\\msohtmlclip1\\01\\clip_themedata.thmx" />\r\n<link rel="colorSchemeMapping" href="file:///C:\\DOCUME~1\\user\\LOCALS~1\\Temp\\msohtmlclip1\\01\\clip_colorschememapping.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<w:LatentStyles DefLockedState="false" DefUnhideWhenUsed="true"\r\nDefSemiHidden="true" DefQFormat="false" DefPriority="99"\r\nLatentStyleCount="267">\r\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="0" SemiHidden="false"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Normal" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="9" SemiHidden="false"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="heading 1" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="9" QFormat="t