 at source. In case the tax is deducted please send us the tax challan with the cheque.</em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Discount Policy</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor any executive programme, if more than two executives from the same organisation participate, each additional participant after the first two gets a 30% discount on the programme fee. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Substitutes/Transfers and Refunds </strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you are unable to attend a registered course we will accept a substitute until two working days before the programme. Substitute candidates will be subject to the same selection process as the original candidate. If you wish to cancel your name from a programme, please notify in writing at least five working days before the programme. Course fee will be refunded after deducting an application-processing fee of Rs. 20,000/-. There will be no refund for cancellation received after the withdrawal date or in case of no-show.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nIt is possible to transfer to another programme within 2 years. The deposited fee will be carried forward after deducting the application-processing fee of Rs. 20,000/-. Please note that only one transfer is permitted. After 2 years the deposited fee will be forfeited. Transfers should be notified at least five working days before the programme.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAll notifications of cancellations, substitutes and transfers must be confirmed in writing.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNote: REDC may cancel or postpone a programme due to insufficient enrolment or unforeseen circumstances. In this case, University will refund registration fee and is not responsible for any other related charges/expenses including cancellation/change charges by airlines and travel agencies. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn case of postponement, the fee may be transferred to the rescheduled offering of that programme or any other programme as an alternate to refund. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe University reserves the right to make changes in its programme policies and fees at any time. <br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'Senior Managers', NULL, 'Yes', 'N', 'Y', 0, 'a'),
(13, 19, 'Programme on Enterprise Systems', '2010-05-18', '2010-05-20', '2010-04-27', 'LUMS, Lahore', '<p>According to one estimate, more than 200 organisations in Pakistan have installed or are in the process of installing &ldquo;Enterprise Systems &ndash;ES&rdquo; (also called ERP systems &ndash; &ldquo;Enterprise Resource Planning&rdquo;).&nbsp; These range from banks to textile mills and MNCs to locally-owned medium-sized firms.&nbsp; Why?&nbsp; Is it &ldquo;strategic&rdquo; or &ldquo;operational&rdquo; &ndash; or both? And, how?</p>', '<p>What exactly are the benefits?&nbsp; Why does it sometimes take a year, and in many cases much longer, along with external consultants to implement these systems?&nbsp; What are the key challenges?&nbsp; They all say &ldquo;requires top management support&rdquo; &ndash; but what must I as a non - IT executive or senior manager do to ensure success by taking the necessary steps before, during and after the implementation process?&nbsp; Answers to these critical questions, and any others that you wish to raise, will be provided during this two-day programme on enterprise systems. There will be opportunity to interact with the senior executives who have played a key part in implementation of ES in organizations in Pakistan.</p>', '<p>Understand the various options involved in leveraging enterprise systems. <br />\r\n-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Selection of technology &ndash; software.<br />\r\n-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Selection of vendor and consultants.<br />\r\n-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Selection of the areas of implementation and their phasing.<br />\r\n-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identification of the methodology options (extent of business process reengineering, for example) <br />\r\n-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Options for designing the project team<br />\r\n-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Options available after implementation to capitalize on the investment.</p>', '<p>This programme is designed for chief executives, general managers and directors. Functional area heads as well as individuals who have been designated to play a leadership role in their organizations&rsquo; efforts to implement enterprise systems can also benefit from this programme.</p>', '<p>The senior faculty of LUMS incorporates the latest research and business concepts into the classroom teaching through <strong>case studies, lectures, video/computer simulations, and small group activities.</strong> We offer an interactive, actioanable learning experience for you to develop personal and professional strengths and lead your organisation into an increasingly competitive environment.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>The case method of teaching is a special strength of LUMS.</strong><br />\r\nThe university is at the forefront in developing and using cases in its various programmes. Cases describe actual business situations and bring into the classroom, problems and opportunities faced by practicing managers. The participants analyse problems, evaluate alternatives and recommend appropriate solutions which help enhance decision-making abilities, and problem-solving skills.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo enrich the learning process REDC faculty shares its experience and knowledge culled from the latest academic literature and research, as well as insights gained from working with companies as researchers, consultants, and board members. The extensive experience of the faculty in planning and conducting executive programmes ensures an interactive and stimulating classroom experience for you.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Peer group learning is an integral part of the learning process</strong>.<br />\r\nThe dynamic exchange of knowledge and experience among successful individuals from different organisations and functions enhances learning. Valuable ideas and insights are shared with fellow participants and faculty in and out of the classroom. Group study provides a forum where you benefit from the diversity of views, perspectives and abilities of other team members. Our programme also provides excellent <strong>networking opportunities.</strong></p>', 59, '<p>Professor, MIS and Management of Technology<br />\r\nPhD, Stanford University<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBefore joining LUMS faculty in 1987, Professor Hassan worked for several computer systems companies in the US on various software and hardware design projects. He has also taught at Stanford University and has a wide range of publications in the areas of information systems, software engineering, management of technology and design automation. He has consulted for the World Bank and UNDP. Currently Dr. Hassan is a charter member of Tie Lahore chapter, Chair of IEEE Lahore section and on the board of AMDISA, Foundation University, HITEC Education City and also a member of HEC Quality and Social Science Committees.</p>', '', '<p><strong>Programme Fee:&nbsp; Rs 48,000</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe fee includes tuition cost, reading material, tea and lunch served during the programme. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you wish to avail accommodation at LUMS, there will be additional fee of <strong>Rs 24,000</strong>. It includes accommodation, breakfasts and dinners for the duration of the programme. However, any extra charges such as telephones, extra meals etc should be paid on departure. You may check-in on the evening preceding the start date of the programme and check out the morning after the programme ends. You are, however, requested to inform us of the time of your arrival and departure.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Accommodation</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe offer single bed accommodation at the Rausing Executive Centre. Each bedroom with attached bathroom is equipped with mini-fridge, writing desk and direct dial STD/ISD telephone and cable TV. All bedrooms at REC are internet-ready. <em>Please note we do not provide accommodation for drivers accompanying participants.</em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Payment</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nPayment is due upon receipt of the acceptance letter along with the invoice. Please ensure that the payment reaches the office BEFORE the start of the programme. Space in the programme may only be ensured after we receive the fee.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur preferred mode of payment is by cheque/banker&rsquo;s draft payable to Lahore University of Management Sciences. Please send the cheque to: <br />\r\n<br />\r\nMarketing Officer &ndash; Executive Education and Development<br />\r\nLahore University of Management Sciences<br />\r\nOpposite Sector &quot;U&quot;, DHA<br />\r\nLahore - 54792<br />\r\nTel: 92-42-35608000<br />\r\nExt.: 8243-8119<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>* The income of the University is exempt from tax under Clause 92 of Second Schedule of the Income Tax Ordinance 2001. Therefore, no tax is deductible from the fee at source. In case the tax is deducted please send us the tax challan with the cheque.</em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Discount Policy</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor any executive programme, if more than two executives from the same organisation participate, each additional participant after the first two gets a 30% discount on the programme fee. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Substitutes/Transfers and Refunds </strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you are unable to attend a registered course we will accept a substitute until two working days before the programme. Substitute candidates will be subject to the same selection process as the original candidate. If you wish to cancel your name from a programme, please notify in writing at least five working days before the programme. Course fee will be refunded after deducting an application-processing fee of Rs. 10,000/-. There will be no refund for cancellation received after the withdrawal date or in case of no-show.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIt is possible to transfer to another programme within 2 years. The deposited fee will be carried forward after deducting the application-processing fee of Rs. 10,000/-. Please note that only one transfer is permitted. After 2 years the deposited fee will be forfeited. Transfers should be notified at least five working days before the programme.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAll notifications of cancellations, substitutes and transfers must be confirmed in writing.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNote: REDC may cancel or postpone a programme due to insufficient enrolment or unforeseen circumstances. In this case, University will refund registration fee and is not responsible for any other related charges/expenses including cancellation/change charges by airlines and travel agencies. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn case of postponement, the fee may be transferred to the rescheduled offering of that programme or any other programme as an alternate to refund. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe University reserves the right to make changes in its programme policies and fees at any time.</p>', 'Senior Managers', NULL, 'Yes', 'N', 'Y', 0, 'a'),
(14, 4, 'Project Management (Lahore)', '2009-12-09', '2009-12-12', '2009-11-18', 'LUMS, Lahore', '<p>Project management has developed into a sophisticated set of tools and techniques, which can help the managers of today to complete their projects on time, within budget and contribute to the overall profitability of the organization. Many projects fail or overrun their cost and time estimates because of poor planning, inadequate allocation of resources, inefficient scheduling of time or simply low commitment from top management.</p>', '<p>This programme will analyze the organizational framework needed for effective project management and identify the techniques that can be used to avoid some of the costly mistakes that many managers make, when they are handling complex projects.</p>', '<p>By the end of the programme, participants would have a clear understanding of the following project management issues:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Planning and Life Cycle<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Role of Project Manager <br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; PERT/Critical Path Method <br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Risk Management <br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Team Building/Leadership<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Managing Conflict <br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Monitoring and Control<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Configuration Management and Rapid Prototyping<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Closure</p>', '<p>This programme is specially designed for managers, engineers and other senior employees responsible for delivering important projects.</p>', '<p>The senior faculty of LUMS incorporates the latest research and business concepts into the classroom teaching through <strong>case studies, lectures, video/computer simulations, and small group activities.</strong> We offer an interactive, actioanable learning experience for you to develop personal and professional strengths and lead your organisation into an increasingly competitive environment.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>The case method of teaching is a special strength of LUMS.</strong><br />\r\nThe university is at the forefront in developing and using cases in its various programmes. Cases describe actual business situations and bring into the classroom, problems and opportunities faced by practicing managers. The participants analyse problems, evaluate alternatives and recommend appropriate solutions which help enhance decision-making abilities, and problem-solving skills.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo enrich the learning process REDC faculty shares its experience and knowledge culled from the latest academic literature and research, as well as insights gained from working with companies as researchers, consultants, and board members. The extensive experience of the faculty in planning and conducting executive programmes ensures an interactive and stimulating classroom experience for you.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Peer group learning is an integral part of the learning process.</strong><br />\r\nThe dynamic exchange of knowledge and experience among successful individuals from different organisations and functions enhances learning. Valuable ideas and insights are shared with fellow participants and faculty in and out of the classroom. Group study provides a forum where you benefit from the diversity of views, perspectives and abilities of other team members. Our programme also provides excellent <strong>networking opportunities</strong>.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 41, '<p>Associate Professor of Operations Management</p>\r\n<p>PhD University of Texas, Arlington</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Professor Khan has designed and delivered numerous executive education programmes for senior executives of local and multinational companies and small and medium enterprises. He has also consulted on ISO 9000implementation.He specializes in a hands-on approach in implementing TQM and has launched several quality and productivity enhancement programmes 