(17, 4, 'Supply Chain Management', '2010-04-13', '2010-04-16', '2010-03-22', 'LUMS, Lahore', '<p>The essence of supply chain management is integrated planning. This includes functional coordination of activities within the firm, among the firm and its vendors, and among the firm and its customers.&nbsp; Along with this is the spatial integration of purchasing, manufacturing, distribution, and inventory management across the countries and continents where it produces and sells its products, as well as enterprise integration of supply chain activities with those concerning demand and corporate financial management. This integrated decision making requires not only the appropriate use of IT along with management tools previously used in optimizing the individual company&rsquo;s performance, but also a few new tools and more significantly a change in the attitudes and the style of management.</p>', '<p>By the end of this course participants would be able to devise an improvement strategy for their Supply Chain.</p>', '<p>The topics covered in this course include:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Building Integrative Partnership Across the Supply Chain<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Forecasting and Uncertainty Management<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Inventory Planning<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT Enabled Supply Chain<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quick Response Retailing/Manufacturing<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Bullwhip Effect<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Aligning Incentives Across the Supply Chain</p>', '<p>The programme is designed for middle and senior managers of companies that are a part of long supply chains. Manufacturers, retailers and distributors for whom the performance of the supply chain is critical to business success are encouraged to apply.</p>', '<p>The senior faculty of LUMS incorporates the latest research and business concepts into the classroom teaching through <strong>case studies, lectures, video/computer simulations, and small group activities. </strong>We offer an interactive, actioanable learning experience for you to develop personal and professional strengths and lead your organisation into an increasingly competitive environment.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>The case method of teaching is a special strength of LUMS.</strong><br />\r\nThe university is at the forefront in developing and using cases in its various programmes. Cases describe actual business situations and bring into the classroom, problems and opportunities faced by practicing managers. The participants analyse problems, evaluate alternatives and recommend appropriate solutions which help enhance decision-making abilities, and problem-solving skills.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo enrich the learning process REDC faculty shares its experience and knowledge culled from the latest academic literature and research, as well as insights gained from working with companies as researchers, consultants, and board members. The extensive experience of the faculty in planning and conducting executive programmes ensures an interactive and stimulating classroom experience for you.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Peer group learning is an integral part of the learning process.</strong><br />\r\nThe dynamic exchange of knowledge and experience among successful individuals from different organisations and functions enhances learning. Valuable ideas and insights are shared with fellow participants and faculty in and out of the classroom. Group study provides a forum where you benefit from the diversity of views, perspectives and abilities of other team members. Our programme also provides excellent <strong>networking opportunities.</strong></p>', 48, '<p>PhD, Rennselaer Polytechnic Institute</p>', '', '<p><strong>Programme Fee: Rs 54,000</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe fee includes tuition cost, reading material, tea and lunch served during the programme. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you wish to avail accommodation at LUMS, there will be additional fee of <strong>Rs 30,000</strong>. It includes accommodation, breakfasts and dinners for the duration of the programme. However, any extra charges such as telephones, extra meals etc should be paid on departure. You may check-in on the evening preceding the start date of the programme and check out the morning after the programme ends. You are, however, requested to inform us of the time of your arrival and departure. </p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Accommodation</strong></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nWe offer single bed accommodation at the Rausing Executive Centre. Each bedroom with attached bathroom is equipped with mini-fridge, writing desk and direct dial STD/ISD telephone and cable TV. We do not provide residence for drivers/attendants accompanying the participants. All bedrooms at REC are internet-ready. <em>Please note we do not provide accommodation for drivers accompanying participants.</em></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Payment</strong></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nPayment is due upon receipt of the acceptance letter along with the invoice. Please ensure that the payment reaches the office BEFORE the start of the programme. Space in the programme may only be ensured after we receive the fee.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur preferred mode of payment is by cheque/banker&rsquo;s draft payable to Lahore University of Management Sciences. Please send the cheque to: <br />\r\n<br />\r\nMarketing Officer &ndash; Executive Education and Development<br />\r\nLahore University of Management Sciences<br />\r\nOpposite Sector &quot;U&quot;, DHA<br />\r\nLahore - 54792<br />\r\nTel: 92-42-5722670-79<br />\r\nExt.: 3223<br />\r\nDirect: 5722142<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em> * The income of the University is exempt from tax under Clause 92 of Second Schedule of the Income Tax Ordinance 2001. Therefore, no tax is deductible from the fee at source. In case the tax is deducted please send us the tax challan with the cheque.<br />\r\n</em><br />\r\n<strong>Discount Policy</strong></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nFor any executive programme, if more than two executives from the same organisation participate, each additional participant after the first two gets a 30% discount on the programme fee. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Substitutes/Transfers and Refunds </strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you are unable to attend a registered course we will accept a substitute until two working days before the programme. Substitute candidates will be subject to the same selection process as the original candidate. If you wish to cancel your name from a programme, please notify in writing at least five working days before the programme. Course fee will be refunded after deducting an application-processing fee of Rs. 10,000/-. There will be no refund for cancellation received after the withdrawal date or in case of no-show.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIt is possible to transfer to another programme within 2 years. The deposited fee will be carried forward after deducting the application-processing fee of Rs. 10,000/-. Please note that only one transfer is permitted. After 2 years the deposited fee will be forfeited. Transfers should be notified at least five working days before the programme.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAll notifications of cancellations, substitutes and transfers must be confirmed in writing.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNote: REDC may cancel or postpone a programme due to insufficient enrolment or unforeseen circumstances. In this case, University will refund registration fee and is not responsible for any other related charges/expenses including cancellation/change charges by airlines and travel agencies. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn case of postponement, the fee may be transferred to the rescheduled offering of that programme or any other programme as an alternate to refund. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe University reserves the right to make changes in its programme policies and fees at any time. </p>', 'Senior Managers', NULL, 'Yes', 'N', 'Y', 4, 'a'),
(18, 4, 'A to Z of Managing Projects: A blended learning approach (Module I)', '2010-04-24', '2010-05-24', '2010-04-02', 'LUMS. Lahore', '<p>Increasingly to gain competitive advantage over others many managers are realizing that advanced skills in project management are an asset.&nbsp; The demand for managers who have the expertise to manage projects which are continuously evolving in complexity and technicality is growing.&nbsp; To help managers acquire in-depth knowledge of project management in the shortest time possible, REDC has developed a new programme <strong>A to Z of Managing Projects</strong> using a blended learning approach.&nbsp; Using web-based distance learning tools and in-class sessions, managers will be able to gain the necessary skills and knowledge to manage projects, facilitate relationships between project team and customers, and balance competing demands of scope, time, cost and quality.</p>', '<p><strong>Module1:</strong>&nbsp;  Which is spread over a month will allow managers to access from their homes or offices using a highly interactive web-based distance learning environment and gain comprehensive knowledge and grounding in the theory of project management.</p>', '<p><strong>Module One </strong></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nProject Integration and Scope Management<br />\r\nProject Cost and Procurement Management<br />\r\nProject Time Management<br />\r\nProject Risk Management<br />\r\n<br />\r\nModule 1 of the programme will be delivered through an e-learning portal. This portal is designed to deliver web-based course material which the participants will be able to access through a username and a password provided by REDC.&nbsp; The course material is highly interactive and conforms to the standards of e-learning. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Forums</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nForums are discussion platforms that provide a time-flexible environment for the participants and their instructors to converse about topics related to project management. The objective of this activity is to create an environment for putting into practice information acquired through e-course.&nbsp; <br />\r\n<br />\r\nApart from this tool, the e-learning portal also provides access to built-in in-site messaging or emailing, announcements regarding class sessions or automatic alerts for starting and ending activities etc.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Technical Requirements</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The e-learning portal has been developed using Net technology on Microsoft IIS and MS SQL Server. The minimum configuration needed to run this module is:</p>\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Desktop PC with 512 MB RAM / PIII 800 MHz. or compatible Processor (preferably a laptop)<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 56K dial-up connection (preferably a broadband connectivity)<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Latest Internet Explorer (other browsers may also be used but some features will be not be functional)<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Flash Player 9.0 +</p>', '<p>The programme is designed for managers, engineers and other executives who would like to get detailed understanding of issues in delivering critical projects.</p>', '<p>The model of e-learning that will provide maximum benefits is given below:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img height="351" width="487" src="/backup/clients/REDC/development/uploads/image(1).jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The above model ensures that learning of participants is enhanced. In line with the model the portal provides a variety of tools such as forums, messaging platforms etc. to the participants that will help them to interact with the other participants as well as with the instructors. The availability of the instructors will be communicated through the Announcement Board at the e-learning portal. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe senior faculty of LUMS incorporates the latest research and business concepts into the classroom teaching through<strong> case studies, lectures, video/computer simulations, and small group activities. </strong>We offer an interactive, actionable learning experience for you to develop personal and professional strengths and lead your organization into an increasingly competitive environment.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>The case method of teaching is a special strength of LUMS.</strong><br />\r\nThe university is at the forefront in developing and using cases in its various programmes. Cases describe actual business situations and bring into the classroom, problems and opportunities faced by practicing managers. The participants analyze problems, evaluate alternatives and recommend appropriate solutions which help enhance decision-making abilities, and problem-solving skills.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nTo enrich the learning process REDC faculty shares its experience and knowledge culled from the latest academic literature and research, as well as insights gained from working with companies as researchers, consultants, and board members. The extensive experience of the faculty in planning and conducting executive programmes ensures an interactive and stimulating classroom experience for you.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Peer group learning is an integral part of the learning process.</strong><br />\r\nThe dynamic exchange of knowledge and experience among successful individuals from different organizations and functions enhances learning. Valuable ideas and insights are shared with fellow participants and faculty in and out of the classroom. Group study provides a forum where you benefit from the diversity of views, perspectives and abilities of other team members. Our programme also provides excellent <strong>networking opportunities.</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 41, '<p>Associate Professor of Operations Management <br />\r\nPhD University of Texas, Arlington</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Professor Khan has designed and delivered numerous executive education programmes for senior executives of local and multinational companies and small and medium enterprises. He has also consulted on ISO 9000implementation.He specializes in a hands-on approach in implementing TQM and has launched several quality and productivity enhancement programmes in a variety of industries in Pakistan. Prior to joining LUMS, Professor Khan taught Operations Research and Management Sciences courses at the University of Texas at Arlington.</p>', '', '<p><strong>Programme Fee:&nbsp; Euros 900&nbsp; </strong></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n(The programme fee is quoted in euros because the distance learning component is offered in collaboration with an international provider).</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nThe fee includes tuition cost, reading material, tea and lunch served during the programme. <br />\r\nIf you wish to avail accommodation at LUMS, there will be additional fee of <strong>Rs 30,000</strong>. It includes accommodation, breakfasts and dinners for the duration of the programme. However, any extra charges such as telephones, extra meals etc should be paid on departure. You may check-in on the evening preceding the start date of the programme and check out the morning after the programme ends. You are, however, requested to inform us of the time of your arrival and departure.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Accommodation</strong></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nWe offer single bed accommodation at the Rausing Executive Centre. Each bedroom with attached bathroom is equipped with mini-fridge, writing desk and direct dial STD/ISD telephone and cable TV. All bedrooms at REC are internet-ready. <em>Please note we do not provide accommodation for drivers accompanying participants.</em></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Payment</strong></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nPayment is due upon receipt of the acceptance letter along with the invoice. Please ensure that the payment reaches the office BEFORE the start of the programme. Space in the programme may only be ensured after we receive the fee.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur preferred mode of payment is by cheque/banker&rsquo;s draft payable to Lahore University of Management Sciences. Please send the cheque to: <br />\r\nMarketing Officer &ndash; Executive Education and Development<br />\r\nLahore University of Management Sciences<br />\r\nOpposite Sector &quot;U&quot;, DHA<br />\r\nLahore - 54792<br />\r\nTel: 92-42-35608000<br />\r\nExt.: 8243-8119<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>* The income of the University is exempt from tax under Clause 92 of Second Schedule of the Income Tax Ordinance 2001. Therefore, no tax is deductible from the fee at source. In case the tax is deducted please send us the tax challan with the cheque.</em></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Discount Policy</strong></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nFor any executive programme, if more than two executives from the same organisation participate, each additional participant after the first two gets a 30% discount on the programme fee.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Substitutes/Transfers and Refunds </strong></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nIf you are unable to attend a registered course we will accept a substitute until two working days before the programme. Substitute candidates will be subject to the same selection process as the original candidate. If you wish to cancel your name from a programme, please notify in writing at least five working days before the programme. Course fee will be refunded after deducting an application-processing fee of Rs. 10,000/-. There will be no refund for cancellation received after the withdrawal date or in case of no-show.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nIt is possible to transfer to another programme within 2 years. The deposited fee will be carried forward after deducting the application-processing fee of Rs. 10,000/-. Please note that only one transfer is permitted. After 2 years the deposited fee will be forfeited. Transfers should be notified at least five working days before the programme.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nAll notifications of cancellations, substitutes and transfers must be confirmed in writing.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nNote: REDC may cancel or postpone a programme due to insufficient enrolment or unforeseen circumstances. In this case, University will refund registration fee and is not responsible for any other related charges/expenses including cancellation/change charges by airlines and travel agencies.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nIn case of postponement, the fee may be transferred to the rescheduled offering of that programme or any other programme as an alternate to refund.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nThe University reserves the right to make changes in its programme policies and fees at any time. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'Senior Managers', NULL, 'Yes', 'N', 'Y', 5, 'a'),
(19, 4, 'A to Z of Managing Projects: A blended learning approach (Module II)', '2010-05-25', '2010-05-28', '2010-04-02', 'LUMS. Lahore', '<p>Increasingly to gain competitive advantage over others many managers are realizing that advanced skills in project management are an asset.&nbsp; The demand for managers who have the expertise to manage projects which are continuously evolving in complexity and technicality is growing.&nbsp; To help managers acquire in-depth knowledge of project management in the shortest time possible, REDC has developed a new programme <strong>A to Z of Managing Projects</strong> using a blended learning approach.&nbsp; Using web-based distance learning tools and in-class sessions, managers will be able to gain the necessary skills and knowledge to manage projects, facilitate relationships between project team and customers, and balance competing demands of scope, time, cost and quality.</p>', '<p><strong>Module 2:</strong>&nbsp; will be 4-day in-class sessions to supplement the fundamental knowledge with the experiential and managerial knowledge delivered through real-life case studies. This approach ensures that participants acquire both the theoretical and practical learning to become well-honed project managers.</p>', '', '', '', 41, '<p>Associate Professor of Operations Management <br />\r\nPhD University of Texas, Arlington</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Professor Khan has designed and delivered numerous executive education programmes for senior executives of local and multinational companies and small and medium enterprises. He has also consulted on ISO 9000implementation.He specializes in a hands-on approach in implementing TQM and has launched several quality and productivity enhancement programmes in a variety of industries in Pakistan. Prior to joining LUMS, Professor Khan taught Operations Research and Management Sciences courses at the University of Texas at Arlington.</p>', '', '', 'Senior Managers', NULL, 'Yes', 'N', 'Y', 6, 'a'),
